  "prompt": "What are the best speeches on humanity?",
  "response": "Here are some of the most powerful and inspirational speeches on humanity:\n\n1. Martin Luther King Jr. - \"I Have a Dream\" (1963)\n- Powerful message of racial equality and human rights\n\n2. Nelson Mandela - Inaugural Speech (1994)\n- Speaks about reconciliation, unity, and human dignity\n\n3. Mahatma Gandhi - \"Quit India\" Speech (1942)\n- Emphasizes non-violence and human compassion\n\n4. Abraham Lincoln - Gettysburg Address (1863)\n- Focuses on human equality and democratic ideals\n\n5. Malala Yousafzai - UN Youth Speech (2013)\n- Advocates for education and human rights, especially for women\n\n6. Charlie Chaplin - \"The Great Dictator\" Speech (1940)\n- Passionate plea for humanity, love, and global unity\n\n7. Eleanor Roosevelt - \"Human Rights\" Speech (1948)\n- Discusses universal human rights and dignity\n\n8. Pope Francis - Address to UN General Assembly (2015)\n- Highlights global human interconnectedness and shared responsibility\n\n9. Kofi Annan - Millennium Summit Speech (2000)\n- Discusses global challenges and human solidarity\n\n10. Elie Wiesel - \"The Perils of Indifference\" Speech (1999)\n- Reflects on human suffering and moral responsibility\n\nThese speeches offer profound insights into human potential, equality, and compassion.",
